Create an EventDetails component to show detailed information about a live event.

Inside a Card, render:

A Text title: "Event Details"

An Avatar displaying the event organizer's profile picture, using the url "https://picsum.photos/100"

A Text with the event title ("React Summit 2025")

A Text with the event description ("A gathering of the brightest minds in React.")

A ProgressBar to show the event's progress (50% complete)

A Checkbox to allow users to opt into receiving event updates

A Button that opens a Modal titled "Event Updates". The modal should contain a Text with details about the event's next steps.

State variables:

"isSubscribed" (boolean)

"showModal" (boolean)